jp.co.rakuten.util.multiindex
クラス MultiIndex<T>

java.lang.Object
  jp.co.rakuten.util.multiindex.MultiIndex<T>
型パラメータ:
T - Target data-type.
public class MultiIndex<T>
extends java.lang.Object

Multi indexable container. 

   Can select indexes from following.
      - SequenceIndex          : by insertion
      - IdentityIndex          : by data-type identity
      - OrderedUniqueIndex     : by unique field
      - OrderedNonUniqueIndex  : by none unique field
      
   Be careful when update associating data,
   because it's necessary to update all indexes.
   So necessary to use modify() or rawModify() function absolutely.
      (There is a possibility to be going to improve in the future.)
      
 == For Example ==
  // Target data-type
  class MyData {
      Integer i1;
      Integer i2;
      String  s1;
      public MyData(Integer i1,Integer i2,String s1){
         this.i1 = i1; this.i2 = i2; this.i3 = i3;
       }
   }
   
  // MultiIndex definition.
  MultiIndex multiIndex = new MultiIndex(
    new IndexBy(
       new SequenceIndex(),
       new IdentityIndex(),
       new OrderedUniqueIndex(MyData.class.getField("i1")),
       new OrderedNonUniqueIndex(MyData.class.getField("i2")),
       new OrderedNonUniqueIndex(MyData.class.getField("s1"))
     )
   );
   
  // Get indexes.
  SequenceIndex sequenceIndex = (SequenceIndex)multiIndex.index(0);
  IdentityIndex identityIndex = (IdentityIndex)multiIndex.index(1);
  OrderedUniqueIndex    i1UniqueIndex    = (OrderedUniqueIndex)multiIndex.index(2); 
  OrderedNonUniqueIndex i2NonUniqueIndex = (OrderedUniqueIndex)multiIndex.index(3); 
  OrderedNonUniqueIndex s1NonUniqueIndex = (OrderedUniqueIndex)multiIndex.index(4);
   
  // Data input.
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(1,10,"d1"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(2,10,"d2"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(3,20,"d1"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(4,20,"d2"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(5,20,"d3"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(6,30,"d1"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(7,30,"d2"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(8,30,"d3"));    
  multiIndex.add(new MyData(9,30,"d4"));    

  // Data find.
  StdIterator>> it = i1UniqueIndex.find(3);
  Record r = it.get().second;
  MyData d = r.get();
  
  // Data remove.
  multiIndex.remove(r);
